    <h2>Districts of Kerala</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card"><h3>Thiruvananthapuram</h3><p>Capital city known for Padmanabhaswamy Temple and Kovalam beach.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kollam</h3><p>Historic port city famous for backwaters and Ashtamudi Lake.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Pathanamthitta</h3><p>Pilgrimage hub with Sabarimala temple and scenic forests.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Alappuzha</h3><p>Known as the "Venice of the East" for its backwaters and houseboats.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kottayam</h3><p>Famous for literacy, publishing, and nearby hill stations.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Idukki</h3><p>Mountain district with tea plantations, dams, and wildlife sanctuaries.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Ernakulam</h3><p>Home to Kochi, a vibrant city blending heritage and modernity.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Thrissur</h3><p>Cultural capital of Kerala with Pooram festival and ancient temples.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Palakkad</h3><p>Gateway to Kerala, rich in paddy fields and historical forts.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Malappuram</h3><p>Historically significant and known for rich Muslim traditions.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kozhikode</h3><p>Historic city where Vasco da Gama landed, rich in spice trade history.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Wayanad</h3><p>Hilly district famous for wildlife, waterfalls, and tribal culture.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kannur</h3><p>Known for Theyyam performances and colonial-era forts.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Kasaragod</h3><p>Northernmost district with Bekal Fort and serene beaches.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

